Rocket trajectories¶

ASE3001: Computational Experiments for Aerospace Engineering, Inha University.
Jong-Han Kim (jonghank@inha.ac.kr)

This example involves the kinematics of a projectile, whose dynamical relations can be described by the following differential equations


\begin{align*} m\dot{V} &= -0.5\rho V^2 S C_d - mg\sin\gamma \\ V\dot{\gamma} &= -g\cos\gamma \\ \dot{R} &= V\cos\gamma \\ \dot{h} &= V\sin\gamma \end{align*}

where $V$, and $\gamma$ represents the speed and the flight path angle of the projectile, where a positive $\gamma$ implies the projectile is going up, and $\gamma=+\pi/2$ implies vertical ascend.

Throughout this problem, you can assume that the gravitational acceleration is constant, $g=9.8m/s^2$, and the air density is well approximated by the following formula.
$$ \rho(h) = 1.225 \left(1-2.256\times 10^{-5}h \right)^{5.256} $$

Suppose a projectile with the following specifications is launched.

  • $m$: mass (=$40kg$)
  • $d$: diameter (=$16cm$)
  • $S$: cross-section area (=$\pi d^2/4$)
  • $C_d$: drag coefficient (=$0.2$)
  • $V(0)$: initial velocity (=$1000m/s$)

(Problem 1) For various initial launch angles, $\gamma(0) = 20,25,\dots, 65, 70$ degrees, plot the vertical trajectory (on $R-h$ plane) and the time history of the projectile's speed.

# your code here

import math
import numpy as np
from scipy.integrate import odeint
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

m = 40               # mass
S = math.pi*0.08**2  # cross-section area
Cd = 0.2             # drag coefficient
g = 9.8              # gravitational acceleration

# function that returns dy/dt=[hdot, vdot]
def model(z,t):
  V, gamma, R, h = z
  rho = 1.225*(1-2.256e-5*h)**5.256

  Vdot = -0.5*rho*V*V*S*Cd/m - g*math.sin(gamma)
  gammadot = -g*math.cos(gamma)/V
  Rdot = V*math.cos(gamma)
  hdot = V*math.sin(gamma)
  return [Vdot, gammadot, Rdot, hdot]

t_list = np.arange(0,1000,0.1)
state_list = np.zeros((len(t_list),4))

fpa_list = np.arange(20,71,5)

for fpa in fpa_list:
  ic = [1000, fpa*math.pi/180, 0, 0]
  state_list[0,:] = ic

  for k in range(len(t_list)-1):
    state = odeint(model,state_list[k,:],[t_list[k],t_list[k+1]])
    state_list[k+1,:] = state[-1,:]
    if state_list[k+1,3]<0:
      break

  plt.figure(num=1, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)
  plt.plot(state_list[:k+1,2]/1000, state_list[:k+1,3]/1000, label=f'FPA={fpa}deg')
  plt.figure(num=2, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)
  plt.plot(t_list[:k+1], state_list[:k+1,0], label=f'FPA={fpa}deg')

plt.figure(num=1, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)
plt.xlabel(r'range (km)')
plt.ylabel(r'altitude (km)')
plt.axis('equal')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()

plt.figure(num=2, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)
plt.xlabel(r'time (sec)')
plt.ylabel(r'speed (m)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()
plt.show()

(Problem 3) Suppose you use the projectile for a parcel delivery service for your customers. Then you will probably need to make at least two modifications to your system, since the initial and the final speed of the projectile are too much high. So you decided to use a small engine, that will slowly accelerate the projectile in the beginning, and a small parachute that decelerates the projectile when it reaches the target. Your parachute deploys when $h\le 1000m$ and $\gamma\le 0$

So your model now looks like,

\begin{align*} m\dot{V} &= -0.5\rho V^2 S C_d - mg\sin\gamma + T \\ V\dot{\gamma} &= -g\cos\gamma \\ \dot{R} &= V\cos\gamma \\ \dot{h} &= V\sin\gamma \end{align*}

with

$$ T = \begin{cases} 4000N & \text{if } t \le 5 s\\ 0 & \text{otherwise} \end{cases} $$

and $$ C_{d}= \begin{cases} 10 & \text{if } \gamma\le 0 \text{ and } h\le 1000m \\ 0.2 & \text{otherwise} \end{cases} $$

Find a sample trajectory when

  • $m$: mass (=$40kg$)
  • $d$: diameter (=$16cm$)
  • $S$: cross-section area (=$\pi d^2/4$)
  • $V(0)$: initial velocity (=$10$)
  • $\gamma(0)$: launch angle (=$50\text{deg}$)

# your code here

# function that returns dy/dt=[hdot, vdot]
def model(z,t):
  V, gamma, R, h = z
  rho = 1.225*(1-2.256e-5*h)**5.256
  T, Cd = 0, 0.2
  if t<5:
    T = 4000
  if gamma<0 and h<1000:
    Cd = 10
  Vdot = -0.5*rho*V*V*S*Cd/m - g*math.sin(gamma) + T/m
  gammadot = -g*math.cos(gamma)/V
  Rdot = V*math.cos(gamma)
  hdot = V*math.sin(gamma)
  return [Vdot, gammadot, Rdot, hdot]

t_list = np.arange(0,1000,0.1)
state_list = np.zeros((len(t_list),4))

fpa = 50
ic = [10, fpa*math.pi/180, 0, 0]
state_list[0,:] = ic

for k in range(len(t_list)-1):
  state = odeint(model,state_list[k,:],[t_list[k],t_list[k+1]])
  state_list[k+1,:] = state[-1,:]
  if state_list[k+1,3]<0:
    break

plt.figure(num=1, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)
plt.plot(state_list[:k+1,2]/1000, state_list[:k+1,3]/1000, label=f'FPA={fpa}deg')
plt.xlabel(r'range (km)')
plt.ylabel(r'altitude (km)')
plt.axis('equal')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()
plt.show()

plt.figure(num=2, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)
plt.plot(t_list[:k+1], state_list[:k+1,0], label=f'FPA={fpa}deg')
plt.xlabel(r'time (sec)')
plt.ylabel(r'speed (m)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()
plt.show()

# function that returns dy/dt=[hdot, vdot]
def model(z,t):
  V, gamma, R, h = z
  rho = 1.225*(1-2.256e-5*h)**5.256
  T, Cd = 0, 0.2
  if t<5:
    T = 4000
  if gamma<0 and h<1000:
    Cd = 10
  Vdot = -0.5*rho*V*V*S*Cd/m - g*math.sin(gamma) + T/m
  gammadot = -g*math.cos(gamma)/V
  Rdot = V*math.cos(gamma)
  hdot = V*math.sin(gamma)
  return [Vdot, gammadot, Rdot, hdot]

t_list = np.arange(0,1000,0.1)
state_list = np.zeros((len(t_list),4))

fpa = 44.1
ic = [10, fpa*math.pi/180, 0, 0]
state_list[0,:] = ic

for k in range(len(t_list)-1):
  state = odeint(model,state_list[k,:],[t_list[k],t_list[k+1]])
  state_list[k+1,:] = state[-1,:]
  if state_list[k+1,3]<0:
    break

print(f'Initial launch angle: {fpa}(deg)')
print(f'Landing at: {state_list[k,2]/1000}(km)')
print(f'Delivery time: {t_list[k]}(sec)')
print(f'Maximum altitude: {np.max(state_list[:,3])/1000}(km)')

plt.figure(num=1, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)
plt.plot(state_list[:k+1,2]/1000, state_list[:k+1,3]/1000, label=f'FPA={fpa}deg')
plt.xlabel(r'range (km)')
plt.ylabel(r'altitude (km)')
plt.axis('equal')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()
plt.show()

plt.figure(num=2, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)

plt.grid()

plt.xlabel(r'time (sec)')
plt.ylabel(r'flight path angle (deg)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()
plt.show()

plt.figure(num=2, figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)
plt.subplot(211)
plt.plot(t_list[:k+1], state_list[:k+1,2]/1000, label=f'FPA={fpa}deg')
plt.xlabel(r'time (sec)')
plt.ylabel(r'range (km)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()

plt.legend()
